&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;constitutional&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The power of Judicial Review in India is constitutional, derived from Articles such as Article 13 (Laws inconsistent with Constitution) and Article 32 (Right to constitutional remedies).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The Supreme Court and High Courts have the authority to review laws and executive actions for their constitutionality.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Judicial Review ensures the supremacy of the Constitution and protects fundamental rights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1) unconstitutional: Incorrect, it is explicitly constitutional.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2) extra-constitutional: Incorrect, not beyond the Constitution.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;4) None of these: Incorrect, as it is constitutional.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assam&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Baishagu is a prominent festival celebrated by the Bodo tribe in Assam.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This festival marks the beginning of the Assamese New Year and is celebrated during the mid-April.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Baishagu involves traditional dance forms such as the Bwisagu dance, performed to the tunes of traditional musical instruments.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The festival is characterized by rituals that honor the local deities and ancestors, as well as community feasting and merrymaking.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is one of the most vibrant and significant cultural festivals in Assam, reflecting the rich heritage of the Bodo community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bodo Tribe:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Bodos are one of the largest ethnic and linguistic groups in Assam, belonging to the Bodo-Kachari community.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They speak the Bodo language, which is recognized as one of the 22 scheduled languages of India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Bodo people primarily inhabit the Bodoland Territorial Region in Assam.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assamese New Year:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Assamese New Year, also known as Rongali Bihu, is celebrated in mid-April.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It marks the beginning of the agricultural cycle, especially the onset of the sowing season.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Rongali Bihu is a time of joy and festivities, involving traditional music, dance, and feasts.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Traditional Music and Dance:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Bwisagu dance is performed during Baishagu with traditional Bodo musical instruments like kham (drum) and sifung (flute).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Dance and music are integral parts of the festival, showcasing the cultural richness of the Bodo community.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cultural Significance:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Festivals like Baishagu play a crucial role in preserving and promoting the cultural heritage of indigenous communities.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They foster community bonding and provide an opportunity to pass traditions and customs to younger generations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Manipravalam.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Lilatilakam &lt;/strong&gt;was written in the Manipravalam language and was a&lt;strong&gt; fourteenth-century text.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manipravalam language:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Manipravalami is a South Indian macaronic language documented in some texts.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a hybrid language that blends Sanskrit vocabulary with Tamil morpho-syntax and is commonly written in the Grantha script.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;However, the Sanskrit text Lilatilakam, written in the 14th century, claims that Manipravalam is a hybrid of Tamil and Sanskrit.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brahmi Script:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Brahmi is the mother script of most of the present Indian scripts including Devanagari, Bengali, Tamil, Malayalam, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It developed into two broad types in Northern and Southern India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;More angular in Northern India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;More circular in Southern India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It was deciphered in 1837 by James Princep.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: Rock-cut edicts of Asoka.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
